## Color System

**Build a token-based palette. Never hardcode hex values in components.**

```css
:root {
  /* Surface hierarchy — 3 levels minimum */
  --surface-base: #0f0f11;       /* canvas / outermost */
  --surface-raised: #17171a;     /* cards, panels */
  --surface-overlay: #1f1f23;    /* modals, dropdowns */

  /* Border */
  --border-subtle: rgba(255,255,255,0.06);
  --border-default: rgba(255,255,255,0.10);
  --border-strong: rgba(255,255,255,0.18);

  /* Text */
  --text-primary: #f0f0f2;
  --text-secondary: #8a8a9a;
  --text-tertiary: #55556a;

  /* Signal — one color, used sparingly */
  --accent: #5b8def;
  --accent-subtle: rgba(91,141,239,0.12);

  /* Semantic */
  --success: #34c77b;
  --warning: #f59f2a;
  --danger: #f2453d;
}
```

**Rules:**
- Max **one accent color**. Secondary actions use ghost/outline styles, not a second hue.
- Avoid gradients on interactive elements — they communicate "decoration," not "action."
- Use opacity variants of the accent for hover/focus states, not lightness shifts.
- Backgrounds must have at minimum 3 distinct surface levels (base → raised → overlay).

