## Motion & Interaction

**Less is more. Every animation must earn its place.**

```css
/* Global easing tokens */
:root {
  --ease-out: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);     /* entrances */
  --ease-in: cubic-bezier(0.7, 0, 0.84, 0);       /* exits */
  --ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1); /* playful bounce */
  --duration-fast: 120ms;
  --duration-base: 200ms;
  --duration-slow: 320ms;
}
```

**Rules:**
- Page transitions: **fade + slide up (8px)**, `duration-slow`, `ease-out`. Never full-page flips.
- Modals: **scale from 0.96 to 1 + fade**, not slide-in from edge.
- List items appearing: **stagger 30ms** between items, `translateY(6px) → 0`.
- Hover states: `duration-fast`. Never animate on hover longer than 150ms — it feels sluggish.
- **Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`**: wrap all non-essential animations.

```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *, *::before, *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

