## Accessibility Baseline (Non-Negotiable)

- All interactive elements reachable via keyboard (`Tab`, `Enter`, `Space`, `Esc`)
- Focus rings visible — never `outline: none` without a custom replacement
- Color contrast: 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text and UI components (WCAG AA)
- All images and icon-only buttons have `alt` / `aria-label`
- Form inputs have associated `<label>` elements

---

## Anti-Patterns (Never Do These)

| Pattern | Why It's Bad | Do This Instead |
|---|---|---|
| Purple gradient hero in a dashboard | Marketing aesthetic in product context | Flat surface with structural color |
| Cards with border-radius > 16px | Looks toy-like in dense UIs | 8–12px for cards |
| Centered full-page layouts for dashboards | Wastes horizontal space, breaks scanning | Left-anchored grid with sidebar |
| Spinner for every loading state | Disorienting for layout-level content | Skeleton loaders |
| Tooltip-as-label | Fails keyboard/screen reader users | Visible label above input |
| Success toast auto-dismissed in 2s | User misses confirmation | 4–6s, manually dismissible |
| Placeholder as only hint text | Disappears on focus | Label always visible, hint text below |
| Multi-color accent palette | Visual noise, no hierarchy | One accent + semantic colors only |
| All-caps body text | Reduces readability | All-caps for labels/metadata only |
| `font-weight: 500` as primary emphasis | Not perceivably different from 400 | Jump to 600 or 700 for true emphasis |

